docs\api-reference.md:331:A failure in any tick phase (commands, spatialSync, systems, resources, diff, listeners) marks the world as **poisoned**:
docs\api-reference.md-332-
docs\api-reference.md-333-- `world.isPoisoned(): boolean` returns `true` until the next call to `recover()`.
docs\api-reference.md-334-- While poisoned, `world.step()` throws `WorldTickFailureError` and `world.stepWithResult()` returns a `WorldStepResult` with `failure.code === 'world_poisoned'`. The original failure that caused the poison is preserved on the result for diagnostics.
