docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-25_2026-04-25.md-53-- **Gemini / Iter-1 regression:** `detectInPlaceMutations` defaults to `true` so strict mode still pays the C1 cost (R1); `findNearest` still O(R³) (R2 perf side); `world.grid` still mutable (R3a). Plus new: resource-transfer FIFO greedy starvation (M_NEW4); path-cache double-clone (L_NEW2).
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-25_2026-04-25.md-54-- **Codex / Iter-1 regression:** M10 still impossible (deferred-by-design, R5); `getEvents` falls back to live ref on stringify failure (R3b); `EntityManager.fromState` only validates `freeList` (R4). Plus new: snapshot `serialize`/`deserialize` alias caller-owned objects (C_NEW1, called Critical); poison contract scope only blocks `step()` (H_NEW2); typed registries lost at callbacks (H_NEW3); `setMeta` accepts NaN/Infinity (M_NEW2); `registerComponent` stores caller-owned options by reference (L_NEW7).
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-25_2026-04-25.md:55:- **Opus / Iter-1 regression:** L11 from iter-1 is actually a correctness bug — `findNearest` `maxRadius` is Chebyshev for a Euclidean filter, so on any 4×4-or-bigger grid entities at the diagonal corner silently return `undefined` (R2 correctness). Plus new: listener exceptions in `processCommands`/`emitTickFailure` bypass the poison contract (H_NEW1); `recover()` doesn't drain commands or events queued during the failed tick (M_NEW1); pathfinding pushes overcost neighbors onto heap (M_NEW3); `getLastTickFailure` deep-clones every call (M_NEW5); `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify())` instead of `structuredClone` (L_NEW1); `addTagInternal`/`setMetaInternal` no alive check on snapshot load (L_NEW4); `recover()` doesn't reset `nextCommandResultSequence` (L_NEW5); `findNearest` early-out comment misleading (L_NEW6).
