docs\superpowers\specs\2026-04-06-client-protocol-design.md:85:- The adapter stores the `onDiff` listener function as a private field so `disconnect()` can remove the exact reference.
docs\superpowers\specs\2026-04-06-client-protocol-design.md:86:- A `connected` boolean flag prevents duplicate listeners on repeated `connect()` calls.
docs\superpowers\specs\2026-04-06-client-protocol-design.md-87-- The `tick` message is constructed inside the `onDiff` callback. Events are captured via `world.getEvents()` at that point (which is inside `executeTick`, after systems run but before the tick ends, so events from the current tick are available).
docs\superpowers\specs\2026-04-06-client-protocol-design.md-88-- The adapter does not manage its own lifecycle — the consumer is responsible for calling `connect()` and `disconnect()` at the right times.
