docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\opus.md-37-- **Why it matters**: The whole point of the v0.4.0 H_NEW1 fix was to make `getEvents` return a defensive copy. The fallback creates a footgun where the contract holds in the common case but silently breaks for exactly the inputs most likely to need it.
