docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\opus.md-54-### `cloneTickFailure` and `cloneTickDiff` use `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...))` instead of `structuredClone`
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\opus.md-55-- **File**: `src/world.ts:2228-2237`
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\opus.md:56:- **Problem**: Both functions are documented (or commented) as deep-clone helpers and both pay the full JSON serialization cost. `structuredClone` is available natively on Node 18+ (the engine's documented minimum) and is roughly 2-5× faster for JSON-shaped data; it also handles circular references safely. Since these helpers run inside `getDiff`/`getLastTickFailure`/`onDiff`-listener paths, every tick may run them.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\opus.md-57-- **Suggested fix**: Replace with `structuredClone(diff)` / `structuredClone(failure)`. Remove the JSON-safety comment (structuredClone doesn't need it) — but keep `assertJsonCompatible` on the *write* path so the structuredClone result is still serializable.
