docs\architecture\drift-log.md-20-| 2026-04-06 | Added behavior tree framework        | Standalone generic BT with ECS-compatible state (BTState) and game-defined TContext    |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-21-| 2026-04-10 | Added RTS-scale standalone primitives | OccupancyGrid, queued grid path helpers, VisibilityMap, and benchmark harness |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-22-| 2026-04-10 | Added render projection and debugger helpers | RenderAdapter for renderer-facing projections and WorldDebugger with probe support |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md:23:| 2026-04-10 | Hardened engine invariants           | Added JSON-safe component/resource state, entity refs, explicit write APIs, read-only grid exposure, resource snapshot v2, package exports/build, and CI |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-24-| 2026-04-11 | Added scenario runner harness        | `runScenario()` for deterministic setup/run/check orchestration over the AI-facing debug/history surfaces |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-25-| 2026-04-12 | Added 6 engine ergonomics features | Typed component registry, loose system typing, world-level state store, spatial query helpers, system ordering constraints, entity tags & metadata — addressing civ-sim-web integration friction |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-26-| 2026-04-23 | Added BT interrupt affordances and semantic diff mode | Address civ-sim-web feedback: reactive selector/sequence + clearRunningState helper; per-component diffMode opt-in to suppress blind-rewrite diff churn |
--
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-30-| 2026-04-25 | ComponentStore.detectInPlaceMutations option | Lets callers opt out of the per-tick all-entries fingerprint scan when they only mutate via setComponent. Strict-mode set() also no longer computes fingerprint redundantly. |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-31-| 2026-04-25 | GameLoop.step no longer auto-advances | World.runTick now calls gameLoop.advance() directly so the gameLoop tick aligns with the diff tick when listeners fire. GameLoop is internal-only (not in src/index.ts). |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md-32-| 2026-04-25 | findNearest correctness + snapshot isolation (v0.4.1) | findNearest maxRadius now `ceil(hypot(W-1,H-1))` so diagonal-corner entities are reachable; serialize/deserialize structuredClone component data and state values to isolate snapshots from live engine state. |
docs\architecture\drift-log.md:33:| 2026-04-25 | Removed in-place mutation auto-detection (v0.5.0, breaking) | `ComponentStoreOptions.detectInPlaceMutations`, `WorldConfig.detectInPlacePositionMutations`, `World.markPositionDirty`, the per-tick spatial sync scan, and `WorldMetrics.spatial.fullScans`/`scannedEntities`/`durationMs.spatialSync` all removed. All mutations must go through `setComponent`/`setPosition`. `world.grid` is now a runtime-immutable read-only delegate. `EventBus.emit` rejects non-JSON payloads. |
