docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-15-| World          | `src/world.ts`           | Top-level API, owns all subsystems, phased system pipeline, metrics, spatial index sync |
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-16-| EntityManager  | `src/entity-manager.ts`  | Entity creation/destruction, ID recycling via free-list, generation counters           |
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-17-| ComponentStore | `src/component-store.ts` | Sparse array storage per component type, generation counter for change detection       |
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md:18:| SpatialGrid    | `src/spatial-grid.ts`    | Sparse occupied-cell grid plus read-only view, neighbor/radius queries                 |
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-19-| GameLoop       | `src/game-loop.ts`       | Fixed-timestep loop, step() for testing, start()/stop() for real-time, speed multiplier, pause/resume |
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-20-| EventBus       | `src/event-bus.ts`       | Typed pub/sub event bus, per-tick buffer, listener registry                            |
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-21-| CommandQueue   | `src/command-queue.ts`   | Typed command buffer, push/drain interface                                             |
--
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-78-- **World** is the only public entry point. EntityManager, ComponentStore, GameLoop are internal implementation details.
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-79-- **Systems** are pure functions `(world: World) => void` or registration objects with a `phase` and `name`. Phases are intentionally lightweight and ordered as `input`, `preUpdate`, `update`, `postUpdate`, `output`.
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-80-- **Components** are pure data interfaces. No methods, no inheritance.
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md:81:- **SpatialGrid** is a sparse map of occupied cells and is synced automatically by World's internal spatial index routine. User systems read grid state via `world.grid.getAt()` / `world.grid.getNeighbors()` / `world.grid.getInRadius()`. The `world.grid` property exposes only a read-only view.
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-82-- **GameLoop** handles timing only. It knows nothing about entities, components, or systems.
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-83-- **EventBus** is owned by World. Systems emit and subscribe via `world.emit()` / `world.on()`. External consumers read events via `world.getEvents()` between ticks. Do not call `eventBus.clear()` directly — World handles this.
docs\architecture\ARCHITECTURE.md-84-- **CommandQueue** is owned by World. External code submits commands via `world.submit()` or `world.submitWithResult()`, registers validators via `world.registerValidator()`, and registers handlers via `world.registerHandler()`. Do not access the queue directly.
--
