docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md:154:- **What's wrong:** `world.grid`, `getAt()`, `getEvents()`, `getDiff()`, `getByTag()`, `getByMeta()` return live engine internals typed as `ReadonlyArray`/`ReadonlySet`/`ReadonlyMap`. No runtime protection — any `as any` cast or naive renderer adapter can mutate them.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md:155:- **Recommended fix:** For the highest-blast-radius getters (`getEvents`, `getDiff`), return a shallow copy. For Sets, return a frozen iterable view. For `world.grid`, wrap in a small object that exposes only the query methods. Internal callers that need direct access should use the private fields, not the public getters.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md-156-
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md-157-### M2. Components can appear simultaneously as `set` and `removed` in `TickDiff` — ✅
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md-158-**Reviewer:** Gemini (Medium).
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md-159-
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md-160-- **File:** `src/component-store.ts:37-44, 49-56`.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md:161:- **What's wrong:** When a component is `remove()`d the entity is added to `removedSet`. If a subsequent `set()` runs in the same tick, the entity is added to `dirtySet` but **not** removed from `removedSet`. `getDirty()` then returns the entity in both `set` and `removed` arrays. A downstream consumer that processes removals after sets will incorrectly delete the just-added component.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\REVIEW.md-162-- **Recommended fix:** In `ComponentStore.set()`, call `this.removedSet.delete(entityId)`. Add a focused test: remove → set in the same tick produces only `set`.
