docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.md-27-### “Read-only” public views are only type-level and remain mutable at runtime
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.md-28-- **File**: `src/world.ts:240-278,731-735,880-881,1030-1034`; `src/spatial-grid.ts:57-90`; `src/event-bus.ts:42-46`
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.md:29:- **Problem**: `world.grid` is the actual `SpatialGrid` instance, `getAt()` returns the backing `Set`, `getEvents()` returns the backing event buffer, `getDiff()` returns the live diff object, and tag getters return backing sets. All are typed as read-only, but none are protected at runtime.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.md-30-- **Why it matters**: Any JS consumer, `any` cast, or careless adapter can mutate engine internals while bypassing `World`, which violates the documented boundary and can corrupt sync/debug state.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.md:31:- **Suggested fix**: Return defensive views. Examples: clone arrays/objects in `getEvents()` and `getDiff()`, return copied/frozen sets from `getAt()`/tag getters, and wrap `world.grid` in an object that only exposes query methods.
