docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\gemini.md-21-- **Iter-1 ID**: M1
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\gemini.md-22-- **File**: `src/world.ts:281`
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\gemini.md:23:- **Problem**: The fix correctly secured `getEvents`, `getByTag`, etc., by returning copies, but left `world.grid` as a direct reference to the internal `SpatialGrid` instance (`this.grid = this.spatialGrid;`). It is only "read-only" via TypeScript types.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\gemini.md:24:- **Why it matters**: A renderer adapter or AI agent can still bypass the type system (`(world.grid as any).insert(...)`) and corrupt the spatial index.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\2\raw\gemini.md-25-- **Suggested fix**: Wrap the spatial grid in a lightweight proxy or object that only delegates the read methods: `this.grid = { width: this.spatialGrid.width, height: this.spatialGrid.height, getAt: (x, y) => this.spatialGrid.getAt(x, y), getNeighbors: ... }`.
