docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log:444:- **Codex** (OpenAI): `codex exec -m gpt-5.4 -c model_reasoning_effort="high" -s read-only --skip-git-repo-check -o <out_file> "<prompt>"`. The config-default model `gpt-5.5` is rejected by the installed CLI on a ChatGPT account; `gpt-5.4` is the strongest model that works. Use `codex exec` (not `codex review`, which only diffs against a base).
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log:445:- **Gemini** (Google): `gemini -m gemini-3.1-pro-preview -p "<prompt>" --approval-mode plan -o text > <out_file>`. `--approval-mode plan` is read-only. `gemini-3.1-pro-preview` is the strongest available model.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log-446-- **Claude Opus 4.7 (1M)** (Anthropic, in-session): use the Agent tool with `model: "opus"` and `subagent_type: "general-purpose"`. The 1M-context window lets a single agent ingest the full codebase.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log-447-- Same prompt across providers so findings are comparable. Run all three in parallel (background Bash for codex/gemini, Agent tool for Opus) and wait for every output before writing the synthesis doc.
