docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log:18685:- **Problem**: `world.grid` is the actual `SpatialGrid` instance, `getAt()` returns the backing `Set`, `getEvents()` returns the backing event buffer, `getDiff()` returns the live diff object, and tag getters return backing sets. All are typed as read-only, but none are protected at runtime.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log-18686-- **Why it matters**: Any JS consumer, `any` cast, or careless adapter can mutate engine internals while bypassing `World`, which violates the documented boundary and can corrupt sync/debug state.
docs\reviews\full\2026-04-25\1\raw\codex.stdout.log:18687:- **Suggested fix**: Return defensive views. Examples: clone arrays/objects in `getEvents()` and `getDiff()`, return copied/frozen sets from `getAt()`/tag getters, and wrap `world.grid` in an object that only exposes query methods.
