docs/api-reference.md-1442-
docs/api-reference.md-1443-Advances the simulation by exactly one tick and returns a structured success/failure result instead of throwing on runtime failure. This is the preferred stepping API for AI loops and remote harnesses.
docs/api-reference.md-1444-
docs/api-reference.md:1445:If the world is poisoned (a previous tick failed and `recover()` has not been called), `stepWithResult()` immediately returns `{ ok: false, failure: { code: 'world_poisoned', ... } }` without attempting another tick.
docs/api-reference.md-1446-
docs/api-reference.md:1447:#### `isPoisoned()`
docs/api-reference.md-1448-
docs/api-reference.md-1449-```typescript
docs/api-reference.md:1450:isPoisoned(): boolean
docs/api-reference.md-1451-```
docs/api-reference.md-1452-
docs/api-reference.md:1453:Returns `true` while the world is in a post-failure poisoned state. Cleared by `recover()`. See Tick failure semantics.
docs/api-reference.md-1454-
docs/api-reference.md:1455:#### `recover()`
docs/api-reference.md-1456-
docs/api-reference.md-1457-```typescript
docs/api-reference.md:1458:recover(): void
docs/api-reference.md-1459-```
docs/api-reference.md-1460-
docs/api-reference.md:1461:Clears the poison flag along with cached `lastTickFailure`, `currentDiff`, and `currentMetrics`. After `recover()` the world is safe to step again. The next successful tick uses a tick number one greater than the failed tick (failed ticks consume their tick number).
