docs/api-reference.md-1580-Submits a command. All registered validators for this command type are run immediately (synchronously). If any validator rejects, the command is not queued.
docs/api-reference.md-1581-
docs/api-reference.md-1582-**Returns:** `true` if the command passed all validators and was queued, `false` if rejected. This is the compatibility wrapper over `submitWithResult()`.
docs/api-reference.md-1583-
docs/api-reference.md:1584:When `instrumentationProfile` is `'minimal'` or `'release'` and no command-result listeners are attached, `submit()` takes a boolean fast path and does not allocate a `CommandSubmissionResult`. Use `submitWithResult()` when the caller explicitly needs the structured outcome.
docs/api-reference.md-1585-
